						               													<description>The game contains:&amp;#10;1 wooden board&amp;#10;80 double-sided (red and black) numbered tiles from 1 to 8&amp;#10;Book with 100 puzzles&amp;#10;Single-player and multiplayer instructions&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic information:&amp;#10;There are 8 lines, 6 circles, and 1 head.&amp;#10;The HEAD is contained of 8 main squares and extra 4 squares showing the directions as a reminder. All 8 main squares should contain the numbers from 1 to 8.&amp;#10;Direction of each line always starts from inside out. Each LINE has 8 squares in total (2 squares inside the head and 6 squares outside the head). Each line should contain the numbers from 1 to 8.&amp;#10;Each CIRCLE should contain the numbers from 1 to 8. All 6 circles are located outside of the head. Each circle is formed of 8 squares connected&amp;#10;with thin lines.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Each number from 1 to 8 can appear only once inside the head.&amp;#10;     Each number from 1 to 8 can appear only once in a single line.&amp;#10;     Each number from 1 to 8 can appear only once in a circle outside the head.&amp;#10;     HIGH TIDE, LOW TIDE, CARIBBEAN, AEGEAN, PACIFIC, ATLANTIC, INDIAN  and ARCTIC line can appear only once in a single game. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;MULTIPLAYER&amp;#10;Set up the board according to the puzzles from the book.&amp;#10;Set a stopwatch for each player and measure the time.&amp;#10;FOR EXAMPLE&amp;#10;If there are three players:&amp;#10;Each player takes a separate wooden board, and the fastest player wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SINGLE PLAYER&amp;#10;Set up the board according to the puzzles from the book.&amp;#10;Set a stopwatch and measure the time.&amp;#10;You become a pro once you solve the puzzles within the following minutes:&amp;#10;BEGINNER &amp;lt; 3&amp;#10;EASY &amp;lt; 4&amp;#10;MEDIUM &amp;lt; 6&amp;#10;HARD &amp;lt; 8&amp;#10;EXPERT &amp;lt; 10&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
